author: @ieilajaimes1154
text:
Pregunta, por qué esta canción aparece como interpretada por Blackpink en los creditos y no como una cancion de Rosé en solo?. De hecho no esta en su perfil de Spotify solitario de ella. O sea me parece q las voces q estan atras algunas pareciera como Jisoo, pero la prota aqui es mi Rosita no entiendo.

Igual q en diciembre le hicieron mucha promo, juraria q iban a sacar una canción de Rosé para su perrito en navidad o algo así. Pero instead Quede 🤡, cuando una vez mas le dieron canciones a Jennie y a Lisa de navidad q nisiquiera tuvieron mucha promoción. Siento q le hacen medio el feo a la Golden Voice del Kpop. Gracias a dios su carrera en solitario sera algo aparte de YG xq enserio q me parece q mi Rosi pierde mucho el tiempo con ellos enserio.

author: @Allie.5.4.6
text:
رغم ان روزي هي التي غنت اغنية بل كامل، ألا ان اغنية مسجلة باسم بلاكبينك. 
لانها في البوم لل فرقة وليس البوم منفرد لل روزي.

author: @Allie.5.4.6
text:
هذا اغنية هي اول اغنية منفردة لعضوة من بلاكبينك في البوم لل فرقة.
حيث ان جميع اغاني بلاكبينك صابقة كانت لجميع اضوات اربعة معن.
ولكن هذا لا يعني ان اغنية لم تعجبني.

You go to a song. Then you like a few comments and also a video. You write a few comments. NO emojis! The more you write, the better. Write a lot of comments. Listen to the whole song. It should not automatically skip to the next video. You need to disable it. Thats it.

author: @Minavis_Penguin
text:
I don't know why none of the comments are not talking about the lyrics that Rosé constructed. The lyrics of this song is telling that you really want to fully love that person but you have a doubt that you're not able to fulfill it and chose to reject his affection and confession meant to be given for you either before or after the commitment because you don't want him to have high expectations from you that you two will last but instead, this song portrays that you should tell him in an early pace that you're not able to give it all as he might end up hurting himself.

All of us want to love and to be loved by someone but sometimes, we're unsure of it if we could give them the enjoyment from us so it's better to think of it and cut that bound between you two rather hurting someone at the other end from expecting your love to them and this song wrote and sang by Rosé is a perfect example.

text: Mình là fan BLackpink đối với BTS tuy k thích lắm có thể là do gì ăn mặc và thể loại âm nhạc của họ k hợp với mình, nhưng k thể phủ nhận tài năng và cố gắng của họ. Hype là một cty tuyệt vời, nếu BP được nâng đỡ như cách Hybe làm với BTS thì mình tin các chị sẽ còn thành công hơn.

author: @cheese_kad
text:
It may sound unfair for Jisoo to not have her solo song in ‘Born Pink’. But the thing is that Rosé has nothing to do with the criticism that people have been labeling and putting on her. All the members agree with Rosé’s solo song in this album, and YG is actually the one that didn’t tell us about a solo song in the first place. 
So please, people, don’t be so tough to Rosé. She herself deserves the song in every aspect. You cannot deny this. Her voice is so angelic and beautiful. 
Wait for Jisoo’s solo! Support and respect each of their work, guys!
